-- Central Termica Offers to Buy Back $25 Million of 2015 Bonds
-- B y   P a b l o   G o n z a l e z
-- 2012-07-16T16:53:10Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-16/central-termica-offers-to-buy-back-25-million-of-2015-bonds.html
Central Termica Loma de la Lata SA,
an Argentine electricity generator owned by  Pampa Energia SA (PAMP) ,
will buy back as much as $25 million of outstanding 2015 notes.  Central Termica is offering to pay 4.70 pesos ($1.03) per
dollar for the bonds, according to a filing to the  Buenos Aires 
stock exchange. The offer began today and will end on July 20 at
3 p.m. in Buenos Aires.  Loma de la Lata has $166.1 million of 2015 unsecured notes
outstanding, according to data compiled by Bloomberg.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Pablo Gonzalez in Buenos Aires at 
 pgonzalez49@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Attwood at 
 jattwood3@bloomberg.net  